# Form SS-4 (EIN Application)

Prepare a complete, line-accurate IRS Form SS-4 using verified formation and operational data.

## Prerequisites

1. Formation documents: articles/certificate, operating agreement/bylaws, amendments
2. Legal name and trade name evidence (DBA/fictitious name filings if any)
3. Mailing and physical addresses (with county/parish)
4. Responsible party identity and SSN/ITIN (or foreign status)
5. Entity classification and any tax elections (e.g., Form 2553/8832, if applicable)
6. Start/acquisition date and accounting year-end month
7. Business activity description and proposed NAICS code
8. Hiring plan: first wage date and projected employee counts
9. Third-party designee details and signer authority (if used)

## Output Structure / Process

Deliverables:
- Completed Form SS-4 with all lines populated or marked N/A where allowed
- Assumptions and discrepancy log (only if sources conflict or are missing)
- Optional cover letter/transmittal memo (if requested)

Process checklist:
- [ ] Extract names, dates, and addresses verbatim from source documents
- [ ] Verify responsible party matches governing documents and has signing authority
- [ ] Confirm entity classification and any tax elections are supported by records
- [ ] Draft business activity narrative and validate NAICS code selection
- [ ] Complete signature block and preparer section (if applicable)
- [ ] Run quality-control consistency checks

Form SS-4 line map (use current IRS version and labels):
| Line(s) | Field | Source / Rules |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Header | Form revision and OMB | Use current IRS SS-4 version |
| 1 | Legal name | Exact from formation docs; match punctuation and suffix |
| 2 | Trade name/DBA | Only if registered; otherwise blank |
| 3 | Mailing address | Include street/P.O. Box, city, state, ZIP, county/parish |
| 4a-4b | Physical address | Must be street address; no P.O. Box |
| 5a-7b | Responsible party | Individual with ultimate control; SSN/ITIN or foreign indicator |
| Entity type | Entity classification | Check the single IRS-defined box that matches the entity |
| S-corp / exempt status | Elections | Only if supported by Form 2553/1023/1024 evidence |
| Start/acquisition | Business start date | Use formation or acquisition date |
| Reason | Primary reason | Choose the single primary trigger for EIN |
| Wages | First wage date | Use actual/anticipated date or N/A if no employees |
| Year-end | Closing month | From governing docs or accountant; default December if none |
| Employees | Next 12 months | Provide realistic max counts: agricultural and other |
| Activity | Principal business | Specific product/service description |
| NAICS | 6-digit code | Most specific match to principal activity |
| Designee | Third-party | Only if authorized; include 5-digit PIN |
| Signature | Authorized signer | Proper title and authority per governing documents |
| Preparer | Paid preparer | Complete only if a paid preparer is used |

Business activity template:
```text
Principal business activity:
- Primary revenue source:
- Products/services:
- Customer segment:
- Delivery channel/operations:
NAICS code:
- 6-digit code:
- Rationale for match:
```

Quality-control checklist:
- [ ] Line 1 matches formation document character-for-character
- [ ] Mailing vs physical address correctly separated
- [ ] Responsible party is an individual with ultimate control
- [ ] Entity type aligns with formation documents and elections
- [ ] Reason for applying aligns with timeline and narrative
- [ ] Wage date is provided if employees will be paid
- [ ] NAICS code reflects the principal revenue activity
- [ ] Signature title matches governing documents

## Guidelines

- Use only verified data from authoritative documents; do not guess SSNs/ITINs or dates.
- If documents conflict, flag the discrepancy and require resolution before finalizing.
- Do not list a P.O. Box as the physical address.
- For foreign responsible parties without SSN/ITIN, follow current IRS SS-4 instructions for foreign status.
- Keep narratives specific and business-accurate; avoid generic labels like “consulting” or “retail.”
- Confirm any tax election references (Form 2553/8832/1023/1024) with supporting records.
- Jurisdiction: U.S. federal IRS form; always align to the latest IRS SS-4 instructions and revision.
